For example, to control devices in public places, we had a project in which we thought about gestures, but not about sweeping ones, but about such meager, short ones.
At the same time, the gestures were not filmed with the camera of the device, but with a wristband that recorded the movements of bones and muscles.
While it is large, but theoretically it can be reduced to the size of a wristwatch.
